<subSubSection box="[151,839,1014,1037]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,839,1014,1037]" box="[151,839,1014,1037]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1014,1036]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">
<typeStatus box="[151,203,1014,1036]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Dujardin, 1839" authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1839" box="[295,555,1014,1037]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Nais" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis box="[295,397,1016,1037]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">Nais picta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dujardin, F." box="[402,555,1014,1036]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" pagination="287 - 294" refId="ref12745" refString="Dujardin, F. (1839) Observations sur quelques Annelides marines. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, Paris, Ser. 2, 11, 287 - 294." type="journal article" year="1839">Dujardin, 1839</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by subsequent designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1081,1934]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1081,1106]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body elongated, not divided into distinct regions; ventral groove and two lateral grooves present. Segments indistinctly annulated. Prostomium broadly rounded, palpode absent; subdermal eyespots; a pair of large, eversible nuchal organs divided into a ventral and a dorsal region. Branchiae entirely absent. Segmental lateral eyes present between parapodia. Parapodial lobes reduced, notopodial and neuropodial capillaries emerging from body wall. Interparapodial ciliated sensory pits present and a ventral lobe may be present. Noto- and neuropodial lappets absent. Noto- and neuropodial small fascicles of simple capillary chaetae. Pygidium with short anal funnel bearing marginal papillae and a pair of basal papillae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1081,1934]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1333,1358]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman, O." box="[321,500,1333,1358]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" pagination="1 - 628" refId="ref13049" refString="Hartman, O. (1959) Catalogue of the polychaetous annelids of the world. Parts 1 and 2. Allan Hancock Foundation Occasional Paper, 23, 1 - 628." type="journal article" year="1959">Hartman (1959)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized thirteen 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Quatrefages" authorityYear="1850" box="[756,938,1333,1358]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[756,938,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">Polyophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dujardin, 1839)" authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1839" baseAuthorityName="Dujardin" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1089,1379,1333,1358]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[1089,1184,1334,1357]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. pictus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dujardin, F." box="[1198,1370,1333,1358]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" pagination="287 - 294" refId="ref12745" refString="Dujardin, F. (1839) Observations sur quelques Annelides marines. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, Paris, Ser. 2, 11, 287 - 294." type="journal article" year="1839">Dujardin, 1839</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The author only considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Kukenthal, 1887" authorityName="Kukenthal" authorityYear="1887" box="[413,717,1369,1394]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis box="[413,524,1370,1393]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. striatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kukenthal, W." box="[530,717,1369,1394]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" pagination="361 - 373" refId="ref13264" refString="Kukenthal, W. (1887) Die Opheliaceen der expedition der Vettore Pisani. Jenaische Zeitschrift fur Naturwissenschaft, 21, 361 - 373." type="journal article" year="1887">Kükenthal, 1887</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid and distinct species from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dujardin" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1118,1212,1370,1393]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[1118,1212,1370,1393]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Michaelsen, W." box="[1226,1436,1369,1394]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref13355" refString="Michaelsen, W. (1892) Polychaeten von Ceylon. Jahrbuch der Hamburgischen wissenschaftlichen Anstalten, 9 (2), 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1892">Michaelsen (1892)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1892" box="[267,436,1405,1430]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="longisetosus">
<emphasis box="[267,436,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. longisetosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a specimen collected in the pelagic environment with long capillaries on last five segments and it was most likely an epitoke. The species 
<taxonomicName authority="Purschke, Ding &amp; Muller, 1995" authorityName="Purschke, Ding &amp; Muller" authorityYear="1995" box="[843,1384,1441,1466]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="qingdaoensis">
<emphasis box="[843,1020,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. qingdaoensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Purschke, G. &amp; Ding, Z. &amp; Muller, M. C." box="[1028,1384,1441,1466]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" pagination="229 - 241" refId="ref13839" refString="Purschke, G., Ding, Z. &amp; Muller, M. C. (1995) Ultrastructural differences as a taxonomic marker: the segmental ocelli of Polyophthalmus pictus and Polyophthalmus qingdaoensis sp. n. (Polychaeta, Opheliidae). Zoomorphology, 115 (4), 229 - 241. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00393803" type="journal article" year="1995">Purschke, Ding &amp; Müller, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was recently described and distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dujardin" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[644,739,1478,1501]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[644,739,1478,1501]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mostly on the basis of the ultrastructure, size, position and number of the segmental eyes (ocelli), and number of anal papillae. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sene Silva, G." box="[938,1146,1513,1538]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" refId="ref14104" refString="Sene Silva, G. (2007) Filogenia de Opheliidae (Annelida: Polychaeta). Unpublished Thesis presented for the degree, Doctor of Sciences, in Zoology, Universidade Federal do Parana, Curitiba, Brazil, 95 pp." type="book" year="2007">Sene Silva (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, in an unpublished Ph.D. dissertation, examined the 
<typeStatus box="[453,501,1550,1574]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartman, 1960" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1960" box="[639,973,1549,1574]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="translucens">
<emphasis box="[639,797,1549,1574]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. translucens</emphasis>
Hartman, 1960
</taxonomicName>
and suggested it should be synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Stop-Bowitz, 1948" authorityName="Stop-Bowitz" authorityYear="1948" box="[216,711,1585,1610]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="abranchiata">
<emphasis box="[216,473,1585,1610]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">Ophelina abranchiata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stop-Bowitz, C." box="[488,711,1585,1610]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" pagination="3 - 58" refId="ref14147" refString="Stop-Bowitz, C. (1948) Sur les polychetes arctiques des familles des Glyceriens, des Opheliens, des Scalibregmiens et des Flabelligeriens. TromsO Museums Arshefter, 66, 3 - 58." type="journal article" year="1948">Stop-Bowitz, 1948</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Purschke, G. &amp; Ding, Z. &amp; Muller, M. C." box="[730,1122,1585,1610]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" pagination="229 - 241" refId="ref13839" refString="Purschke, G., Ding, Z. &amp; Muller, M. C. (1995) Ultrastructural differences as a taxonomic marker: the segmental ocelli of Polyophthalmus pictus and Polyophthalmus qingdaoensis sp. n. (Polychaeta, Opheliidae). Zoomorphology, 115 (4), 229 - 241. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00393803" type="journal article" year="1995">Purschke, Ding &amp; Müller (1995)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Purschke, Ding &amp; Muller" authorityYear="1995" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="qingdaoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">Polyophthalmus qingdaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on ultrastructural differences of the segmental eyes and discussed that several 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Quatrefages" authorityYear="1850" box="[1257,1436,1621,1646]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1257,1436,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">Polyophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species synonymized with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dujardin" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[445,537,1658,1681]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[445,537,1658,1681]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could actually be valid. Until now, three species are considered as valid: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dujardin" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1337,1429,1658,1681]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[1337,1429,1658,1681]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Purschke, Ding &amp; Muller" authorityYear="1995" box="[151,322,1693,1718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="qingdaoensis">
<emphasis box="[151,322,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. qingdaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blake &amp; Maciolek 2016 a)" authorityName="Blake &amp; Maciolek" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Blake &amp; Maciolek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[381,836,1693,1718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="translucens">
<emphasis box="[381,533,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. translucens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Blake, J. A. &amp; Maciolek, N. J." box="[547,828,1693,1718]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" refId="ref12381" refString="Blake, J. A. &amp; Maciolek, N. J. (2016 a) Opheliidae Malmgren, 1867. In: Westheide, W. &amp; Purschke, G. (Eds), Handbook of Zoology. pp. 10, De Gruyter, Available from: https: // www. degruyter. com / view / Zoology / bp _ 029147 - 6 _ 74 (accessed September 2018)" type="url" year="2016">Blake &amp; Maciolek 2016a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. A taxonomic revision of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dujardin" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1158,1249,1694,1717]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Polyophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opheliida" pageId="11" pageNumber="220" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[1158,1249,1694,1717]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex would be desirable including intra- and interspecific variability but also molecular data, whenever possible. There are very few morphological features and body pigmentation has been the main character used to separate species. However, this feature seems to be variable among populations and the pigmentation can also fade in preserved material. The segmental origin of the lateral eyes and its extent in segments, length of capillaries on anterior and posterior end, number and 
<typeStatus box="[445,503,1874,1898]" pageId="11" pageNumber="220">types</typeStatus>
of capillaries per parapodium, parapodial structures, and number of pygidial papillae should also be comparatively examined.
</paragraph>
